{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \"FW-M15-005|result indexing|suite packaging|artifact lineage|suite outputs\" agent_tickets docs src tests'","aggregated_output":"docs/milestones.md:988:- result indexing  \ndocs/experiment_orchestration_design.md:159:This ticket intentionally freezes vocabulary before full suite packaging lands.\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_design.md:215:- suite packaging and indexing\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-002_rationale.md:31:suite packaging. This planner therefore normalizes intent and deterministic\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-002_rationale.md:84:- `FW-M15-005` can persist the planned artifact roots as one suite-owned index\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-003_rationale.md:41:`FW-M15-005`.\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-003_rationale.md:89:- `FW-M15-005`: promote the execution-state artifact inventory into a canonical\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-003_rationale.md:90:  suite packaging and indexing layer\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-001_rationale.md:37:that would overlap with `FW-M15-005`.\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-001_rationale.md:43:- later suite packaging must reuse the artifact roles and lineage semantics\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-001_rationale.md:71:- suite-owned output-root packaging and result indexing\ndocs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-001_rationale.md:91:- `FW-M15-005`: package suite outputs and result indexes under a suite-owned\nagent_tickets/fruit_fly_surface_wave_project_compendium.md:829:result indexing\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:122:## FW-M15-005 - Package suite outputs with deterministic storage conventions, result indexing, and artifact lineage\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:132:Add the packaging and indexing layer for Milestone 15 suite outputs. Define deterministic output locations, one authoritative suite metadata anchor, shared discovery helpers for suite-cell records and stage artifacts, and a result index that maps normalized dimension values plus ablation identity to downstream simulator, analysis, validation, dashboard, and report artifacts. The first version should expose both machine-friendly discovery and reviewer-friendly inventory surfaces, but it should avoid inventing a second source of truth for experiment-level artifacts that already have their own bundle contracts.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:135:- There is one canonical Milestone 15 suite packaging layer with deterministic output paths, metadata-backed discovery, and stable artifact references for suite cells and stage outputs.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:140:- A companion rationale note is added at `docs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-005_rationale.md` and explicitly explains design choices, testing strategy, simplifications, and future expansion points.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:147:Assume `FW-M15-001` through `FW-M15-004` and the Milestone 12 through Milestone 14 bundle contracts are already in place. This ticket should make result indexing and storage conventions explicit enough that later review tooling never has to guess which artifact belongs to which suite cell. Do not attempt to create a git commit as part of this ticket.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:156:Milestone 12 already packages experiment-level summaries and Milestone 13 already packages validation findings, but Milestone 15 is specifically about comparing whole suites and ablations rather than inspecting one experiment at a time. There is still no canonical suite-level workflow that can aggregate across seeds, collapse repeated cells deterministically, line up baseline versus wave or intact versus ablated comparisons, and produce one comparison-ready table surface keyed by the dimensions that matter. Without that rollup layer, result indexing alone will not make the outcomes easy to compare, and every reviewer will end up building bespoke notebooks to answer routine questions about whether an ablation changed the shared metrics, wave diagnostics, or validation status.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:174:Assume `FW-M15-001` through `FW-M15-005` and the Milestone 12 plus Milestone 13 packaging layers are already in place. Keep the first aggregation layer honest and inspectable; reviewers should be able to trace any reported suite-level delta back to packaged experiment-level evidence. Do not attempt to create a git commit as part of this ticket.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:213:Perform a senior-level verification pass over the completed Milestone 15 implementation and publish a concise readiness report in-repo. The pass should exercise the full local suite workflow end to end on fixture artifacts and at least one representative manifest-driven suite path, verify that the declared contract matches shipped behavior across suite planning, batch execution, ablation derivation, suite packaging, rollup computation, and reporting, and record any remaining scientific or engineering risks that later showcase or deeper scientific sweep work must respect. Fix defects or documentation drift directly where reasonable, and turn the rest into explicit follow-on tickets rather than leaving them implicit.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-003_Build_explicit_surface-graph_and_patch-graph_artifacts_for_the_multiresolution_morphology_bundle/stdout.jsonl:48:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Plan:\\n1. Refactor `src/flywire_wave/mesh_pipeline.py` so patchification covers the full simplified surface deterministically, then serialize separate fine-surface and coarse-patch artifacts with explicit membership/mapping arrays.\\n2. Extend the manifest record in library code to expose processed-artifact lineage back to the raw mesh and skeleton files instead of leaving that relationship implicit.\\n3. Add a fixture-driven regression that builds assets from a local stub mesh, loads the `.npz` bundles, and checks filenames, array keys, graph shapes, coverage of the fine-to-coarse mapping, and repeat-run determinism.\\n4. Run the targeted build test and then `make test` to confirm the broader pipeline still passes.\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-004_Implement_fair_P0_and_P1_baseline_neuron_families_with_shared_readout_semantics/stdout.jsonl:41:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_20\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"FW-M9-001|synaptic integration current|explicit delay structure|reduced baseline|P1|delay structure|integration current\\\" agent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md docs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml agent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-001* agent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-002* agent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-003*'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:31:    P1: Stronger reduced baseline using an effective-point or reduced-compartment model with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:41:      statement: Survival against the stronger reduced baseline P1.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:106:    name: Survival against stronger reduced baseline P1\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:107:    description: Confirm that the shared-output effect is not explained away by a stronger reduced baseline with explicit integration current or delay structure.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:115:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus baseline P1/intact, with the same comparison available under shuffled topology\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:116:    expected_relationship: The Milestone 1 effect remains detectable against P1, not only against P0.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:118:      - baseline P1 arm\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:122:    notes: No numeric margin is locked yet; only the requirement that the effect survive the stronger reduced baseline.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:188:    description: P0 versus P1 baseline challenge plot for the same observable family.\\ndocs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md:37:- `P1` means the stronger reduced baseline: an effective-point or reduced\\ndocs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md:38:  compartment realization that may add explicit synaptic integration current or\\ndocs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md:39:  deterministic delay structure, but still on the same connectome slice and the\\ndocs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md:45:- `P1`: `P0` plus extra internal integration state and optional deterministic\\ndocs/simulator_result_bundle_design.md:138:columns, or a different meaning for `P0`/`P1`, that is a new contract version,\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:10:## FW-M9-001 - Freeze a versioned simulator result bundle contract and fair baseline design note\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:20:Define a first-class simulator result bundle contract in library code and document the baseline-model design choices behind it. Centralize run-path construction, metadata serialization, and output discovery so baseline and later `surface_wave` runs can share the same high-level bundle shape. The design note should be decisive: pin down what `P0` and `P1` mean in software terms, define the shared timebase and readout conventions, state what a fair baseline is allowed to add versus what only the wave model may add, and specify the invariants later metrics, UI, and comparison tooling must preserve.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:25:- A dedicated markdown design note compares the supported baseline families, chooses the default `P0` and `P1` realizations, documents shared readout conventions, and names the invariants later `surface_wave` and UI work must preserve.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:60:Assume `FW-M9-001` is already in place. Favor script-thin entrypoints and library-owned normalization logic so the same manifest does not acquire a second incompatible execution path later. Before finishing this ticket, stage all changes made for it and create a non-amended commit that includes those changes.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:86:Assume `FW-M9-001` and `FW-M9-002` have landed. Keep the runtime boring, explicit, and inspectable; later solver work should be able to trust the orchestration layer rather than work around it. Before finishing this ticket, stage all changes made for it and create a non-amended commit that includes those changes.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:88:## FW-M9-004 - Implement fair P0 and P1 baseline neuron families with shared readout semantics\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:95:The Milestone 1 design lock explicitly names `P0` and `P1`, but the repo still has no actual implementation of either baseline family. There is no library-owned equation set, parameter schema, update rule, normalization convention, or shared readout mapping for the canonical point baseline versus the stronger reduced baseline. Without concrete `P0` and `P1` implementations, later comparisons to `surface_wave` will either be scientifically vague or will drift into script-local one-off baselines that nobody can audit fairly.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:98:Implement the baseline neuron-family layer that instantiates the canonical `P0` and `P1` models described by the design lock. `P0` should realize the passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment baseline, while `P1` should realize the stronger reduced baseline with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure chosen in `FW-M9-001`. Expose the realized state variables and readout mapping explicitly so downstream metrics compare fair, shared observables rather than apples to oranges.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:101:- There is one canonical API that resolves normalized model specs into executable `P0` and `P1` neuron-family implementations.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:102:- `P0` and `P1` use documented, test-covered update equations and parameter semantics rather than hidden heuristics or hardcoded constants in runner code.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:109:- A focused unit test that instantiates fixture `P0` and `P1` models, steps them under simple drives, and asserts deterministic responses plus shared readout behavior\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:112:Assume `FW-M9-001` through `FW-M9-003` are already in place. Keep the baseline fair and explicit: the point of this ticket is not maximal biological richness, but a credible comparison family that later reviewers can audit quickly. Before finishing this ticket, stage all changes made for it and create a non-amended commit that includes those changes.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:164:Assume `FW-M9-001` through `FW-M9-005` are already in place. Favor one clean user-facing execution path over multiple half-overlapping scripts; later wave-mode work should extend this workflow, not compete with it. Before finishing this ticket, stage all changes made for it and create a non-amended commit that includes those changes.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_9_baseline_non_wave_simulator_tickets.md:180:- The verification pass checks contract compatibility across manifest planning, runtime execution, `P0` and `P1` behavior, coupling and input integration, result serialization, logging, metrics, and UI-facing payloads.\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-002_Build_manifest-driven_simulation_plans_typed_baseline_config_normalization_and_run_discovery_helpers/stdout.jsonl:6:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/bash -lc 'pwd && rg --files'\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo\\\\nscripts/04_validate_manifest.py\\\\nscripts/11_milestone8a_readiness.py\\\\nscripts/10_stimulus_bundle.py\\\\nscripts/build_registry.py\\\\nscripts/08_coupling_inspection.py\\\\nscripts/01_select_subset.py\\\\nscripts/00_verify_access.py\\\\nscripts/05_preview_geometry.py\\\\nscripts/07_milestone6_readiness.py\\\\nscripts/run_agent_tickets.py\\\\nscripts/09_milestone7_readiness.py\\\\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py\\\\nscripts/03_build_wave_assets.py\\\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py\\\\nscripts/13_milestone8b_readiness.py\\\\nscripts/06_operator_qa.py\\\\nscripts/12_retinal_bundle.py\\\\nagent_tickets/milestone_8b_retinal_ommatidial_sampler_tickets.md\\\\nagent_tickets/milestone_10_surface_wave_engine_tickets.md\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-002_Build_manifest-driven_simulation_plans_typed_baseline_config_normalization_and_run_discovery_helpers/stdout.jsonl\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-002_Build_manifest-driven_simulation_plans_typed_baseline_config_normalization_and_run_discovery_helpers/prompt.md\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-001_Freeze_a_versioned_simulator_result_bundle_contract_and_fair_baseline_design_note/stdout.jsonl\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T044643Z/FW-M9-001_Freeze_a_versioned_simulator_result_bundle_contract_and_fair_